input.content:
# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

This plan adds a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary
real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group
targets, prefixed `!board-name`) and can send direct messages (plain `username` targets). The goal
is a fully-formed, structurally correct bundled channel extension that satisfies the same invariants
as IRC, Nostr, and the other bundled channel plugins — but lives entirely in
`extensions/pulseboard/` with no modifications to any existing file.

**Constraint**: Only new files under `extensions/pulseboard/` may be created.
Consequence: no `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` SDK facade can be added. The `src/runtime-api.ts`
barrel must therefore re-export from individual general `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths directly
instead of a dedicated channel facade (like how `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` works for IRC).

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Plugin / channel ID | `pulseboard` | Must match dir name, package name, channel id per naming invariant |
| Package name | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | `@openclaw/<id>` — no suffix needed |
| `npmSpec` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | Must equal package name per invariant |
| Chat types | `["direct", "group"]` | Supports user DMs and board posts |
| Text chunk limit | `4000` characters | Per spec |
| Board target prefix | `!board-name` | Analogous to IRC `#channel`; distinguishes boards from user DMs |
| DM policy default | `"pairing"` | Safe default, consistent with IRC |
| Group policy default | `"allowlist"` | Safe default, consistent with IRC |
| Gateway | Passive stub (no real network) | Fictional platform — no real SDK to call |
| Send | Stub returning timestamp-based ID | Same reason |

---

## File Structure

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # Plugin manifest
├── package.json                  # NPM package + openclaw channel metadata
├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry
├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry
├── api.ts                        # Public barrel
└── src/
    ├── runtime-api.ts            # Internal SDK re-exports (no dedicated facade)
    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── types.ts                  # Domain types
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schema + buildChannelConfigSchema
    ├── accounts.ts               # Account listing + resolution
    ├── normalize.ts              # Target normalization utilities
    ├── send.ts                   # Outbound send stub
    └── channel.ts                # pulseboardPlugin via createChatChannelPlugin
```

No test files are required for the plan scope, but `src/channel.test.ts` could be added as a
separate follow-up.

---

## File-by-File Specification

### `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest — only `id`, `channels`, and an empty `configSchema` (same as IRC/Nostr):

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Invariant**: `id` = `"pulseboard"` must match the directory name, package name anchor, and
`openclaw.channel.id` in `package.json`.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": { "optional": true }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Boards + DMs)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Real-time bulletin boards with DM and board-post routing.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board", "bulletin-board"],
      "systemImage": "doc.richtext",
      "quickstartAllowFrom": true
    },
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    }
  }
}
```

No runtime `dependencies` block because the platform is fictional — no external SDK is needed. All
imports come from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` (resolved at runtime via `openclaw`).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`

```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "pulseboard",
  name: "PulseBoard",
  description: "PulseBoard channel plugin",
  plugin: pulseboardPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime,
});
```

Mirrors `extensions/irc/index.ts` exactly — no `registerFull` needed (no HTTP routes or gateway
methods for the fictional platform).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`

```typescript
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";

export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseboardPlugin);
```

Identical one-liner pattern used by every bundled channel plugin.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`

```typescript
export * from "./src/accounts.js";
```

Only the account helpers need to be on the public barrel (the same minimal scope IRC uses).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime-api.ts`

Because there is no `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` core facade (which would require modifying a
core file), this barrel imports directly from individual general `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths.
All these subpaths are in `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`.

```typescript
// Internal runtime barrel for the PulseBoard extension.
// Imports from individual plugin-sdk subpaths because no dedicated pulseboard facade exists.

export { getChatChannelMeta } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
export { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
export { buildBaseChannelStatusSummary } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers";
export { createAccountStatusSink } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-lifecycle";
export { PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-status";
export { chunkTextForOutbound } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/reply-chunking";
export type { ChannelPlugin, OpenClawConfig, PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
export type { RuntimeEnv } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-env";
export type { OutboundReplyPayload } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/reply-payload";
export type {
  DmPolicy,
  GroupPolicy,
  MarkdownConfig,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema";
```

> **Note on `chunkTextForOutbound`**: This function is defined in
> `src/plugin-sdk/text-chunking.ts` and re-exported by several channel facades. The `reply-chunking`
> subpath is the most likely general path; verify against the actual export at implementation time.
> If it is not there, a direct import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` (which IS in the entrypoints
> list) is a viable fallback for this specific utility.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "./runtime-api.js";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };

export function clearPulseBoardRuntime(): void {
  setPulseBoardRuntime(undefined as unknown as PluginRuntime);
}
```

Identical structure to `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts`.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

Domain types, importing shared config types from `./runtime-api.js` (keeps types out of core):

```typescript
import type { DmPolicy, GroupPolicy, MarkdownConfig, OpenClawConfig } from "./runtime-api.js";

export type PulseBoardGroupConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  serverUrl?: string;      // PulseBoard server base URL
  username?: string;       // Username on PulseBoard
  token?: string;          // Auth token (plain string; schema uses buildSecretInputSchema)
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  boards?: string[];       // Subscribed board names (without ! prefix)
  groups?: Record<string, PulseBoardGroupConfig>;
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
};

export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// Augments the host OpenClawConfig shape so account resolvers are fully typed
export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  /** Normalized target: board name (with !) for group posts, sender username for DMs. */
  target: string;
  senderUsername: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};
```

No `PulseBoardProbe` type is needed unless a real probe is implemented; the status adapter can
use a generic snapshot for the stub.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/config-schema.ts`

Zod schema following the IRC pattern exactly, using helpers from
`openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema` and `openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod`:

```typescript
import {
  buildChannelConfigSchema,
  DmPolicySchema,
  GroupPolicySchema,
  MarkdownConfigSchema,
  requireOpenAllowFrom,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema";
import { buildSecretInputSchema } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import { z } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod";

const PulseBoardGroupSchema = z
  .object({
    requireMention: z.boolean().optional(),
    enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
    allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
    systemPrompt: z.string().optional(),
  })
  .strict();

const PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase = z
  .object({
    name: z.string().optional(),
    enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
    serverUrl: z.string().optional(),
    username: z.string().optional(),
    token: buildSecretInputSchema().optional(),
    dmPolicy: DmPolicySchema.optional().default("pairing"),
    allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
    defaultTo: z.string().optional(),
    groupPolicy: GroupPolicySchema.optional().default("allowlist"),
    boards: z.array(z.string()).optional(),
    groups: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardGroupSchema.optional()).optional(),
    markdown: MarkdownConfigSchema,
  })
  .strict();

export const PulseBoardAccountSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({
    policy: value.dmPolicy,
    allowFrom: value.allowFrom,
    ctx,
    path: ["allowFrom"],
    message: 'channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy="open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom to include "*"',
  });
});

export const PulseBoardConfigSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.extend({
  accounts: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardAccountSchema.optional()).optional(),
  defaultAccount: z.string().optional(),
}).superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({
    policy: value.dmPolicy,
    allowFrom: value.allowFrom,
    ctx,
    path: ["allowFrom"],
    message: 'channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy="open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom to include "*"',
  });
});

export const PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema = buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardConfigSchema);
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`

Account listing and resolution, following `extensions/irc/src/accounts.ts`:

```typescript
import { createAccountListHelpers, describeAccountSnapshot } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers";
import { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID, normalizeAccountId } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
import { resolveMergedAccountConfig } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution";
import { normalizeResolvedSecretInputString } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import type { CoreConfig, PulseBoardAccountConfig } from "./types.js";

export type ResolvedPulseBoardAccount = {
  accountId: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  name?: string;
  configured: boolean;   // true when serverUrl AND username are both resolved
  serverUrl: string;
  username: string;
  token: string;
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
};

const { listAccountIds: listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveDefaultAccountId: resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId } =
  createAccountListHelpers("pulseboard", { normalizeAccountId });
export { listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId };

function mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(cfg: CoreConfig, accountId: string): PulseBoardAccountConfig {
  return resolveMergedAccountConfig<PulseBoardAccountConfig>({
    channelConfig: cfg.channels?.pulseboard as PulseBoardAccountConfig | undefined,
    accounts: cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.accounts as Record<string, Partial<PulseBoardAccountConfig>> | undefined,
    accountId,
    omitKeys: ["defaultAccount"],
    normalizeAccountId,
  });
}

export function resolvePulseBoardAccount(params: {
  cfg: CoreConfig;
  accountId?: string | null;
}): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount {
  const hasExplicitAccountId = Boolean(params.accountId?.trim());
  const baseEnabled = params.cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.enabled !== false;

  const resolve = (accountId: string): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount => {
    const merged = mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(params.cfg, accountId);
    const enabled = baseEnabled && merged.enabled !== false;

    // Env var fallback for the default account only
    const serverUrl = (
      merged.serverUrl?.trim() ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_SERVER_URL?.trim() : "") ||
      ""
    ).trim();

    const username = (
      merged.username?.trim() ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_USERNAME?.trim() : "") ||
      ""
    ).trim();

    const token =
      normalizeResolvedSecretInputString({ value: merged.token, path: `channels.pulseboard.accounts.${accountId}.token` }) ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_TOKEN?.trim() : "") ||
      "";

    return {
      accountId,
      enabled,
      name: merged.name?.trim() || undefined,
      configured: Boolean(serverUrl && username),
      serverUrl,
      username,
      token,
      config: { ...merged, serverUrl, username },
    };
  };

  const normalized = normalizeAccountId(params.accountId);
  const primary = resolve(normalized);
  if (hasExplicitAccountId) return primary;
  if (primary.configured) return primary;

  const fallbackId = resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId(params.cfg);
  if (fallbackId === primary.accountId) return primary;
  const fallback = resolve(fallbackId);
  return fallback.configured ? fallback : primary;
}

export function listEnabledPulseBoardAccounts(cfg: CoreConfig): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount[] {
  return listPulseBoardAccountIds(cfg)
    .map((accountId) => resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg, accountId }))
    .filter((account) => account.enabled);
}
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/normalize.ts`

Target normalization — distinguishes `!board-name` (group) from plain `username` (DM):

```typescript
/**
 * Returns true if the normalized target is a board (starts with !).
 */
export function isBoardTarget(target: string): boolean {
  return target.startsWith("!");
}

/**
 * Normalizes a PulseBoard target. Boards must start with !.
 * Returns empty string for invalid input.
 *
 * Valid inputs:
 *   "!announcements" → "!announcements"
 *   "announcements"  → "!announcements"   (plain board name, prefix added)
 *   "alice"          → "alice"            (plain username for DMs)
 *   "!alice"         → "!alice"           (explicit board target)
 */
export function normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(input: string): string {
  const trimmed = input.trim().toLowerCase();
  if (!trimmed) return "";
  // Accept explicit board prefix
  if (trimmed.startsWith("!")) {
    const name = trimmed.slice(1).trim();
    return name ? `!${name}` : "";
  }
  // Plain lowercase identifier — could be a username or implicit board
  if (/^[a-z0-9_-]+$/.test(trimmed)) {
    return trimmed;
  }
  return "";
}

/**
 * Heuristic: does the input look like a PulseBoard target ID?
 */
export function looksLikePulseBoardTargetId(input: string): boolean {
  return normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(input) !== "";
}

/**
 * Normalizes an allow-list entry (DM identities are plain usernames only).
 * Returns null for anything that looks like a board name.
 */
export function normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(raw: string): string | null {
  const trimmed = raw.trim().toLowerCase();
  if (!trimmed || trimmed.startsWith("!")) return null;
  return /^[a-z0-9_*-]+$/.test(trimmed) ? trimmed : null;
}
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/send.ts`

Stub send function (no real HTTP call for the fictional platform):

```typescript
import { getPulseBoardRuntime } from "./runtime.js";
import { resolvePulseBoardAccount } from "./accounts.js";
import { normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget } from "./normalize.js";
import type { CoreConfig } from "./types.js";

export type SendPulseBoardOptions = {
  cfg?: CoreConfig;
  accountId?: string;
  replyTo?: string;
};

export type SendPulseBoardResult = {
  messageId: string;
  target: string;
};

export async function sendMessagePulseboard(
  to: string,
  text: string,
  opts: SendPulseBoardOptions = {},
): Promise<SendPulseBoardResult> {
  const runtime = getPulseBoardRuntime();
  const cfg = (opts.cfg ?? runtime.config.loadConfig()) as CoreConfig;
  const account = resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg, accountId: opts.accountId });

  if (!account.configured) {
    throw new Error(
      `PulseBoard is not configured for account "${account.accountId}" ` +
      "(need serverUrl and username in channels.pulseboard).",
    );
  }

  const target = normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(to);
  if (!target) throw new Error(`Invalid PulseBoard target: ${to}`);
  if (!text.trim()) throw new Error("Message must be non-empty for PulseBoard sends");

  // Record outbound activity for status tracking
  try {
    runtime.channel.activity.record({
      channel: "pulseboard",
      accountId: account.accountId,
      direction: "outbound",
    });
  } catch {
    // Tolerate missing runtime during tests
  }

  // Stub: generate a deterministic-ish message ID (no real HTTP call)
  const messageId = `pb-${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 7)}`;
  return { messageId, target };
}
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts`

The main channel plugin. Uses `createChatChannelPlugin` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`. Follows
the IRC `src/channel.ts` structure closely.

**Imports** (all from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` or local `./` files):
- `createChatChannelPlugin`, `getChatChannelMeta`, `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID` → `./runtime-api.js`
- `ChannelPlugin`, `PluginRuntime`, `PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE`, `chunkTextForOutbound`,
  `buildBaseChannelStatusSummary`, `createAccountStatusSink` → `./runtime-api.js`
- `describeAccountSnapshot` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers`
- `formatNormalizedAllowFromEntries` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/allow-from`
- `adaptScopedAccountAccessor`, `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`,
  `createScopedDmSecurityResolver` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers`
- `composeAccountWarningCollectors` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-policy`
- `createChannelDirectoryAdapter`, `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister` →
  `openclaw/plugin-sdk/directory-runtime`
- `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter`, `createDefaultChannelRuntimeState` →
  `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers`

**Key sections of `pulseboardPlugin`**:

```typescript
export const pulseboardPlugin: ChannelPlugin<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount> = createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "pulseboard",
    meta: { ...meta, quickstartAllowFrom: true },

    capabilities: {
      chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
      blockStreaming: true,     // no streaming support (fictional platform)
    },

    reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },
    configSchema: PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema,

    config: {
      ...pulseBoardConfigAdapter,          // createScopedChannelConfigAdapter
      isConfigured: (account) => account.configured,
      describeAccount: (account) => describeAccountSnapshot({
        account,
        configured: account.configured,
        extra: { serverUrl: account.serverUrl, username: account.username },
      }),
    },

    messaging: {
      normalizeTarget: normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget,
      targetResolver: {
        looksLikeId: looksLikePulseBoardTargetId,
        hint: "<username|!board-name>",
      },
    },

    directory: createChannelDirectoryAdapter({
      listPeers: async (params) => listPulseBoardDirectoryPeers(params),   // allow-from users
      listGroups: async (params) => listPulseBoardDirectoryBoards(params), // subscribed boards
    }),

    status: createComputedAccountStatusAdapter({
      defaultRuntime: createDefaultChannelRuntimeState(DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID),
      buildChannelSummary: ({ account, snapshot }) => ({
        ...buildBaseChannelStatusSummary(snapshot),
        serverUrl: account.serverUrl,
        username: account.username,
      }),
      probeAccount: async ({ account }) => ({
        ok: account.configured,
        summary: account.configured
          ? `${account.username} @ ${account.serverUrl}`
          : "not configured",
        serverUrl: account.serverUrl,
        username: account.username,
      }),
      resolveAccountSnapshot: ({ account }) => ({
        accountId: account.accountId,
        name: account.name,
        enabled: account.enabled,
        configured: account.configured,
        extra: { serverUrl: account.serverUrl, username: account.username },
      }),
    }),

    gateway: {
      startAccount: async (ctx) => {
        // Stub: no real WebSocket/HTTP listener for the fictional platform.
        // Just wait for the abort signal so the gateway lifecycle works correctly.
        if (!ctx.account.configured) {
          throw new Error(
            `PulseBoard is not configured for account "${ctx.accountId}" ` +
            "(need serverUrl and username in channels.pulseboard).",
          );
        }
        ctx.log?.info(`[${ctx.accountId}] PulseBoard stub gateway started`);
        await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
          ctx.abortSignal.addEventListener("abort", () => resolve(), { once: true });
        });
      },
    },
  },

  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "pulseboardUser",
      message: PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE,
      normalizeAllowEntry: (entry) => normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(entry),
      notify: async ({ id, message }) => {
        await sendMessagePulseboard(id, message);
      },
    },
  },

  security: {
    resolveDmPolicy: resolvePulseBoardDmPolicy,  // createScopedDmSecurityResolver
  },

  outbound: {
    base: {
      deliveryMode: "direct",
      chunker: chunkTextForOutbound,
      chunkerMode: "markdown",
      textChunkLimit: 4000,
    },
    attachedResults: {
      channel: "pulseboard",
      sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId, replyToId }) =>
        sendMessagePulseboard(to, text, {
          cfg: cfg as CoreConfig,
          accountId: accountId ?? undefined,
          replyTo: replyToId ?? undefined,
        }),
      sendMedia: async ({ cfg, to, text, mediaUrl, accountId, replyToId }) =>
        sendMessagePulseboard(
          to,
          mediaUrl ? `${text}\n\nAttachment: ${mediaUrl}` : text,
          {
            cfg: cfg as CoreConfig,
            accountId: accountId ?? undefined,
            replyTo: replyToId ?? undefined,
          },
        ),
    },
  },
});
```

**Helper objects created at module level** (before `pulseboardPlugin`):

1. `const meta = getChatChannelMeta("pulseboard")` — loads channel metadata from the manifest
2. `const pulseBoardConfigAdapter` — `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount, ...>({ sectionKey: "pulseboard", listAccountIds: listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveAccount: adaptScopedAccountAccessor(resolvePulseBoardAccount), defaultAccountId: resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId, resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom, formatAllowFrom: ..., resolveDefaultTo: (account) => account.config.defaultTo })`
3. `const resolvePulseBoardDmPolicy` — `createScopedDmSecurityResolver<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({ channelKey: "pulseboard", resolvePolicy: (account) => account.config.dmPolicy, resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom, policyPathSuffix: "dmPolicy", normalizeEntry: normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry })`
4. `const listPulseBoardDirectoryPeers` — `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({ kind: "user", resolveAccount: adaptScopedAccountAccessor(resolvePulseBoardAccount), resolveSources: (account) => [account.config.allowFrom ?? []], normalizeId: (entry) => normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(entry) })`
5. `const listPulseBoardDirectoryBoards` — `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({ kind: "group", resolveAccount: adaptScopedAccountAccessor(resolvePulseBoardAccount), resolveSources: (account) => [account.config.boards ?? [], Object.keys(account.config.groups ?? {})], normalizeId: (entry) => { const n = normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(entry); return n && isBoardTarget(n) ? n : null; } })`

---

## Naming Invariant Compliance

The `src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts` checks four rules for every `extensions/*/` directory:

| Rule | Expected | Value | Pass? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Package name anchored to plugin id | `@openclaw/pulseboard` or allowed suffix | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | ✓ |
| Directory name matches manifest id | `pulseboard` | `pulseboard` | ✓ |
| `openclaw.install.npmSpec` = package name | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | ✓ |
| `openclaw.channel.id` = manifest id | `pulseboard` | `pulseboard` | ✓ |

---

## Critical Files to Create (in order)

1. `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`
2. `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`
3. `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime-api.ts`
4. `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`
5. `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`
6. `extensions/pulseboard/src/config-schema.ts`
7. `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`
8. `extensions/pulseboard/src/normalize.ts`
9. `extensions/pulseboard/src/send.ts`
10. `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts`
11. `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`
12. `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`
13. `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`

Create `src/` files first since entry-point files import from them.

---

## Reference Files (do not modify)

| Purpose | Path |
|---|---|
| Closest structural template | `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` |
| Manifest format | `extensions/irc/openclaw.plugin.json` |
| Package.json format | `extensions/irc/package.json` |
| Entry point format | `extensions/irc/index.ts` |
| Setup entry format | `extensions/irc/setup-entry.ts` |
| Config schema pattern | `extensions/irc/src/config-schema.ts` |
| Account resolution pattern | `extensions/irc/src/accounts.ts` |
| Send stub to extend | `extensions/irc/src/send.ts` |
| Runtime store pattern | `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts` |
| Naming invariant tests | `src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts` |
| Available SDK subpaths | `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json` |

---

## Verification

1. **Naming invariants** — run `pnpm test -- src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming` and confirm
   the new `pulseboard` entry passes all four naming checks.

2. **Type checking** — run `pnpm tsgo` (or `pnpm build`) to confirm no TypeScript errors in the
   new files. The TS compiler will catch any SDK import paths that don't resolve or type mismatches
   in the `createChatChannelPlugin` call.

3. **Lint/format** — run `pnpm check` (Oxlint + Oxfmt) from the repo root.

4. **Channel listed** — with minimal config (`channels.pulseboard.serverUrl` +
   `channels.pulseboard.username`), run `openclaw channels status` and confirm PulseBoard appears.

5. **Config validation** — run `openclaw config set channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy pairing` and
   verify it applies without schema errors.

6. **Schema drift check** — run `pnpm config:docs:check` to confirm the config schema baseline
   does not drift unexpectedly.

tool_use_result.content:
# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

This plan adds a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary
real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group
targets, prefixed `!board-name`) and can send direct messages (plain `username` targets). The goal
is a fully-formed, structurally correct bundled channel extension that satisfies the same invariants
as IRC, Nostr, and the other bundled channel plugins — but lives entirely in
`extensions/pulseboard/` with no modifications to any existing file.

**Constraint**: Only new files under `extensions/pulseboard/` may be created.
Consequence: no `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` SDK facade can be added. The `src/runtime-api.ts`
barrel must therefore re-export from individual general `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths directly
instead of a dedicated channel facade (like how `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` works for IRC).

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Plugin / channel ID | `pulseboard` | Must match dir name, package name, channel id per naming invariant |
| Package name | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | `@openclaw/<id>` — no suffix needed |
| `npmSpec` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | Must equal package name per invariant |
| Chat types | `["direct", "group"]` | Supports user DMs and board posts |
| Text chunk limit | `4000` characters | Per spec |
| Board target prefix | `!board-name` | Analogous to IRC `#channel`; distinguishes boards from user DMs |
| DM policy default | `"pairing"` | Safe default, consistent with IRC |
| Group policy default | `"allowlist"` | Safe default, consistent with IRC |
| Gateway | Passive stub (no real network) | Fictional platform — no real SDK to call |
| Send | Stub returning timestamp-based ID | Same reason |

---

## File Structure

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # Plugin manifest
├── package.json                  # NPM package + openclaw channel metadata
├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry
├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry
├── api.ts                        # Public barrel
└── src/
    ├── runtime-api.ts            # Internal SDK re-exports (no dedicated facade)
    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── types.ts                  # Domain types
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schema + buildChannelConfigSchema
    ├── accounts.ts               # Account listing + resolution
    ├── normalize.ts              # Target normalization utilities
    ├── send.ts                   # Outbound send stub
    └── channel.ts                # pulseboardPlugin via createChatChannelPlugin
```

No test files are required for the plan scope, but `src/channel.test.ts` could be added as a
separate follow-up.

---

## File-by-File Specification

### `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest — only `id`, `channels`, and an empty `configSchema` (same as IRC/Nostr):

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Invariant**: `id` = `"pulseboard"` must match the directory name, package name anchor, and
`openclaw.channel.id` in `package.json`.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": { "optional": true }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Boards + DMs)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Real-time bulletin boards with DM and board-post routing.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board", "bulletin-board"],
      "systemImage": "doc.richtext",
      "quickstartAllowFrom": true
    },
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    }
  }
}
```

No runtime `dependencies` block because the platform is fictional — no external SDK is needed. All
imports come from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` (resolved at runtime via `openclaw`).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`

```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "pulseboard",
  name: "PulseBoard",
  description: "PulseBoard channel plugin",
  plugin: pulseboardPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime,
});
```

Mirrors `extensions/irc/index.ts` exactly — no `registerFull` needed (no HTTP routes or gateway
methods for the fictional platform).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`

```typescript
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";

export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseboardPlugin);
```

Identical one-liner pattern used by every bundled channel plugin.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`

```typescript
export * from "./src/accounts.js";
```

Only the account helpers need to be on the public barrel (the same minimal scope IRC uses).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime-api.ts`

Because there is no `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` core facade (which would require modifying a
core file), this barrel imports directly from individual general `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths.
All these subpaths are in `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`.

```typescript
// Internal runtime barrel for the PulseBoard extension.
// Imports from individual plugin-sdk subpaths because no dedicated pulseboard facade exists.

export { getChatChannelMeta } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
export { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
export { buildBaseChannelStatusSummary } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers";
export { createAccountStatusSink } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-lifecycle";
export { PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-status";
export { chunkTextForOutbound } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/reply-chunking";
export type { ChannelPlugin, OpenClawConfig, PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
export type { RuntimeEnv } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-env";
export type { OutboundReplyPayload } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/reply-payload";
export type {
  DmPolicy,
  GroupPolicy,
  MarkdownConfig,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema";
```

> **Note on `chunkTextForOutbound`**: This function is defined in
> `src/plugin-sdk/text-chunking.ts` and re-exported by several channel facades. The `reply-chunking`
> subpath is the most likely general path; verify against the actual export at implementation time.
> If it is not there, a direct import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` (which IS in the entrypoints
> list) is a viable fallback for this specific utility.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "./runtime-api.js";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };

export function clearPulseBoardRuntime(): void {
  setPulseBoardRuntime(undefined as unknown as PluginRuntime);
}
```

Identical structure to `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts`.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

Domain types, importing shared config types from `./runtime-api.js` (keeps types out of core):

```typescript
import type { DmPolicy, GroupPolicy, MarkdownConfig, OpenClawConfig } from "./runtime-api.js";

export type PulseBoardGroupConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  serverUrl?: string;      // PulseBoard server base URL
  username?: string;       // Username on PulseBoard
  token?: string;          // Auth token (plain string; schema uses buildSecretInputSchema)
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  boards?: string[];       // Subscribed board names (without ! prefix)
  groups?: Record<string, PulseBoardGroupConfig>;
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
};

export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// Augments the host OpenClawConfig shape so account resolvers are fully typed
export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  /** Normalized target: board name (with !) for group posts, sender username for DMs. */
  target: string;
  senderUsername: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};
```

No `PulseBoardProbe` type is needed unless a real probe is implemented; the status adapter can
use a generic snapshot for the stub.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/config-schema.ts`

Zod schema following the IRC pattern exactly, using helpers from
`openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema` and `openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod`:

```typescript
import {
  buildChannelConfigSchema,
  DmPolicySchema,
  GroupPolicySchema,
  MarkdownConfigSchema,
  requireOpenAllowFrom,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema";
import { buildSecretInputSchema } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import { z } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod";

const PulseBoardGroupSchema = z
  .object({
    requireMention: z.boolean().optional(),
    enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
    allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
    systemPrompt: z.string().optional(),
  })
  .strict();

const PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase = z
  .object({
    name: z.string().optional(),
    enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
    serverUrl: z.string().optional(),
    username: z.string().optional(),
    token: buildSecretInputSchema().optional(),
    dmPolicy: DmPolicySchema.optional().default("pairing"),
    allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
    defaultTo: z.string().optional(),
    groupPolicy: GroupPolicySchema.optional().default("allowlist"),
    boards: z.array(z.string()).optional(),
    groups: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardGroupSchema.optional()).optional(),
    markdown: MarkdownConfigSchema,
  })
  .strict();

export const PulseBoardAccountSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({
    policy: value.dmPolicy,
    allowFrom: value.allowFrom,
    ctx,
    path: ["allowFrom"],
    message: 'channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy="open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom to include "*"',
  });
});

export const PulseBoardConfigSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.extend({
  accounts: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardAccountSchema.optional()).optional(),
  defaultAccount: z.string().optional(),
}).superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({
    policy: value.dmPolicy,
    allowFrom: value.allowFrom,
    ctx,
    path: ["allowFrom"],
    message: 'channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy="open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom to include "*"',
  });
});

export const PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema = buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardConfigSchema);
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`

Account listing and resolution, following `extensions/irc/src/accounts.ts`:

```typescript
import { createAccountListHelpers, describeAccountSnapshot } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers";
import { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID, normalizeAccountId } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
import { resolveMergedAccountConfig } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution";
import { normalizeResolvedSecretInputString } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import type { CoreConfig, PulseBoardAccountConfig } from "./types.js";

export type ResolvedPulseBoardAccount = {
  accountId: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  name?: string;
  configured: boolean;   // true when serverUrl AND username are both resolved
  serverUrl: string;
  username: string;
  token: string;
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
};

const { listAccountIds: listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveDefaultAccountId: resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId } =
  createAccountListHelpers("pulseboard", { normalizeAccountId });
export { listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId };

function mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(cfg: CoreConfig, accountId: string): PulseBoardAccountConfig {
  return resolveMergedAccountConfig<PulseBoardAccountConfig>({
    channelConfig: cfg.channels?.pulseboard as PulseBoardAccountConfig | undefined,
    accounts: cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.accounts as Record<string, Partial<PulseBoardAccountConfig>> | undefined,
    accountId,
    omitKeys: ["defaultAccount"],
    normalizeAccountId,
  });
}

export function resolvePulseBoardAccount(params: {
  cfg: CoreConfig;
  accountId?: string | null;
}): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount {
  const hasExplicitAccountId = Boolean(params.accountId?.trim());
  const baseEnabled = params.cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.enabled !== false;

  const resolve = (accountId: string): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount => {
    const merged = mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(params.cfg, accountId);
    const enabled = baseEnabled && merged.enabled !== false;

    // Env var fallback for the default account only
    const serverUrl = (
      merged.serverUrl?.trim() ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_SERVER_URL?.trim() : "") ||
      ""
    ).trim();

    const username = (
      merged.username?.trim() ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_USERNAME?.trim() : "") ||
      ""
    ).trim();

    const token =
      normalizeResolvedSecretInputString({ value: merged.token, path: `channels.pulseboard.accounts.${accountId}.token` }) ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_TOKEN?.trim() : "") ||
      "";

    return {
      accountId,
      enabled,
      name: merged.name?.trim() || undefined,
      configured: Boolean(serverUrl && username),
      serverUrl,
      username,
      token,
      config: { ...merged, serverUrl, username },
    };
  };

  const normalized = normalizeAccountId(params.accountId);
  const primary = resolve(normalized);
  if (hasExplicitAccountId) return primary;
  if (primary.configured) return primary;

  const fallbackId = resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId(params.cfg);
  if (fallbackId === primary.accountId) return primary;
  const fallback = resolve(fallbackId);
  return fallback.configured ? fallback : primary;
}

export function listEnabledPulseBoardAccounts(cfg: CoreConfig): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount[] {
  return listPulseBoardAccountIds(cfg)
    .map((accountId) => resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg, accountId }))
    .filter((account) => account.enabled);
}
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/normalize.ts`

Target normalization — distinguishes `!board-name` (group) from plain `username` (DM):

```typescript
/**
 * Returns true if the normalized target is a board (starts with !).
 */
export function isBoardTarget(target: string): boolean {
  return target.startsWith("!");
}

/**
 * Normalizes a PulseBoard target. Boards must start with !.
 * Returns empty string for invalid input.
 *
 * Valid inputs:
 *   "!announcements" → "!announcements"
 *   "announcements"  → "!announcements"   (plain board name, prefix added)
 *   "alice"          → "alice"            (plain username for DMs)
 *   "!alice"         → "!alice"           (explicit board target)
 */
export function normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(input: string): string {
  const trimmed = input.trim().toLowerCase();
  if (!trimmed) return "";
  // Accept explicit board prefix
  if (trimmed.startsWith("!")) {
    const name = trimmed.slice(1).trim();
    return name ? `!${name}` : "";
  }
  // Plain lowercase identifier — could be a username or implicit board
  if (/^[a-z0-9_-]+$/.test(trimmed)) {
    return trimmed;
  }
  return "";
}

/**
 * Heuristic: does the input look like a PulseBoard target ID?
 */
export function looksLikePulseBoardTargetId(input: string): boolean {
  return normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(input) !== "";
}

/**
 * Normalizes an allow-list entry (DM identities are plain usernames only).
 * Returns null for anything that looks like a board name.
 */
export function normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(raw: string): string | null {
  const trimmed = raw.trim().toLowerCase();
  if (!trimmed || trimmed.startsWith("!")) return null;
  return /^[a-z0-9_*-]+$/.test(trimmed) ? trimmed : null;
}
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/send.ts`

Stub send function (no real HTTP call for the fictional platform):

```typescript
import { getPulseBoardRuntime } from "./runtime.js";
import { resolvePulseBoardAccount } from "./accounts.js";
import { normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget } from "./normalize.js";
import type { CoreConfig } from "./types.js";

export type SendPulseBoardOptions = {
  cfg?: CoreConfig;
  accountId?: string;
  replyTo?: string;
};

export type SendPulseBoardResult = {
  messageId: string;
  target: string;
};

export async function sendMessagePulseboard(
  to: string,
  text: string,
  opts: SendPulseBoardOptions = {},
): Promise<SendPulseBoardResult> {
  const runtime = getPulseBoardRuntime();
  const cfg = (opts.cfg ?? runtime.config.loadConfig()) as CoreConfig;
  const account = resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg, accountId: opts.accountId });

  if (!account.configured) {
    throw new Error(
      `PulseBoard is not configured for account "${account.accountId}" ` +
      "(need serverUrl and username in channels.pulseboard).",
    );
  }

  const target = normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(to);
  if (!target) throw new Error(`Invalid PulseBoard target: ${to}`);
  if (!text.trim()) throw new Error("Message must be non-empty for PulseBoard sends");

  // Record outbound activity for status tracking
  try {
    runtime.channel.activity.record({
      channel: "pulseboard",
      accountId: account.accountId,
      direction: "outbound",
    });
  } catch {
    // Tolerate missing runtime during tests
  }

  // Stub: generate a deterministic-ish message ID (no real HTTP call)
  const messageId = `pb-${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 7)}`;
  return { messageId, target };
}
```

