### `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts`

The main channel plugin. Uses `createChatChannelPlugin` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`. Follows
the IRC `src/channel.ts` structure closely.

**Imports** (all from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` or local `./` files):
- `createChatChannelPlugin`, `getChatChannelMeta`, `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID` → `./runtime-api.js`
- `ChannelPlugin`, `PluginRuntime`, `PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE`, `chunkTextForOutbound`,
  `buildBaseChannelStatusSummary`, `createAccountStatusSink` → `./runtime-api.js`
- `describeAccountSnapshot` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers`
- `formatNormalizedAllowFromEntries` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/allow-from`
- `adaptScopedAccountAccessor`, `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`,
  `createScopedDmSecurityResolver` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers`
- `composeAccountWarningCollectors` → `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-policy`
- `createChannelDirectoryAdapter`, `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister` →
  `openclaw/plugin-sdk/directory-runtime`
- `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter`, `createDefaultChannelRuntimeState` →
  `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers`

**Key sections of `pulseboardPlugin`**:

```typescript
export const pulseboardPlugin: ChannelPlugin<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount> = createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "pulseboard",
    meta: { ...meta, quickstartAllowFrom: true },

    capabilities: {
      chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
      blockStreaming: true,     // no streaming support (fictional platform)
    },

    reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },
    configSchema: PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema,

    config: {
      ...pulseBoardConfigAdapter,          // createScopedChannelConfigAdapter
      isConfigured: (account) => account.configured,
      describeAccount: (account) => describeAccountSnapshot({
        account,
        configured: account.configured,
        extra: { serverUrl: account.serverUrl, username: account.username },
      }),
    },

    messaging: {
      normalizeTarget: normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget,
      targetResolver: {
        looksLikeId: looksLikePulseBoardTargetId,
        hint: "<username|!board-name>",
      },
    },

    directory: createChannelDirectoryAdapter({
      listPeers: async (params) => listPulseBoardDirectoryPeers(params),   // allow-from users
      listGroups: async (params) => listPulseBoardDirectoryBoards(params), // subscribed boards
    }),

    status: createComputedAccountStatusAdapter({
      defaultRuntime: createDefaultChannelRuntimeState(DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID),
      buildChannelSummary: ({ account, snapshot }) => ({
        ...buildBaseChannelStatusSummary(snapshot),
        serverUrl: account.serverUrl,
        username: account.username,
      }),
      probeAccount: async ({ account }) => ({
        ok: account.configured,
        summary: account.configured
          ? `${account.username} @ ${account.serverUrl}`
          : "not configured",
        serverUrl: account.serverUrl,
        username: account.username,
      }),
      resolveAccountSnapshot: ({ account }) => ({
        accountId: account.accountId,
        name: account.name,
        enabled: account.enabled,
        configured: account.configured,
        extra: { serverUrl: account.serverUrl, username: account.username },
      }),
    }),

    gateway: {
      startAccount: async (ctx) => {
        // Stub: no real WebSocket/HTTP listener for the fictional platform.
        // Just wait for the abort signal so the gateway lifecycle works correctly.
        if (!ctx.account.configured) {
          throw new Error(
            `PulseBoard is not configured for account "${ctx.accountId}" ` +
            "(need serverUrl and username in channels.pulseboard).",
          );
        }
        ctx.log?.info(`[${ctx.accountId}] PulseBoard stub gateway started`);
        await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
          ctx.abortSignal.addEventListener("abort", () => resolve(), { once: true });
        });
      },
    },
  },

  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "pulseboardUser",
      message: PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE,
      normalizeAllowEntry: (entry) => normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(entry),
      notify: async ({ id, message }) => {
        await sendMessagePulseboard(id, message);
      },
    },
  },

  security: {
    resolveDmPolicy: resolvePulseBoardDmPolicy,  // createScopedDmSecurityResolver
  },

  outbound: {
    base: {
      deliveryMode: "direct",
      chunker: chunkTextForOutbound,
      chunkerMode: "markdown",
      textChunkLimit: 4000,
    },
    attachedResults: {
      channel: "pulseboard",
      sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId, replyToId }) =>
        sendMessagePulseboard(to, text, {
          cfg: cfg as CoreConfig,
          accountId: accountId ?? undefined,
          replyTo: replyToId ?? undefined,
        }),
      sendMedia: async ({ cfg, to, text, mediaUrl, accountId, replyToId }) =>
        sendMessagePulseboard(
          to,
          mediaUrl ? `${text}\n\nAttachment: ${mediaUrl}` : text,
          {
            cfg: cfg as CoreConfig,
            accountId: accountId ?? undefined,
            replyTo: replyToId ?? undefined,
          },
        ),
    },
  },
});
```

**Helper objects created at module level** (before `pulseboardPlugin`):

1. `const meta = getChatChannelMeta("pulseboard")` — loads channel metadata from the manifest
2. `const pulseBoardConfigAdapter` — `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount, ...>({ sectionKey: "pulseboard", listAccountIds: listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveAccount: adaptScopedAccountAccessor(resolvePulseBoardAccount), defaultAccountId: resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId, resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom, formatAllowFrom: ..., resolveDefaultTo: (account) => account.config.defaultTo })`
3. `const resolvePulseBoardDmPolicy` — `createScopedDmSecurityResolver<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({ channelKey: "pulseboard", resolvePolicy: (account) => account.config.dmPolicy, resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom, policyPathSuffix: "dmPolicy", normalizeEntry: normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry })`
4. `const listPulseBoardDirectoryPeers` — `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({ kind: "user", resolveAccount: adaptScopedAccountAccessor(resolvePulseBoardAccount), resolveSources: (account) => [account.config.allowFrom ?? []], normalizeId: (entry) => normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(entry) })`
5. `const listPulseBoardDirectoryBoards` — `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({ kind: "group", resolveAccount: adaptScopedAccountAccessor(resolvePulseBoardAccount), resolveSources: (account) => [account.config.boards ?? [], Object.keys(account.config.groups ?? {})], normalizeId: (entry) => { const n = normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(entry); return n && isBoardTarget(n) ? n : null; } })`

