tool_input.plan:
# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

This plan adds a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary
real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group
targets, prefixed `!board-name`) and can send direct messages (plain `username` targets). The goal
is a fully-formed, structurally correct bundled channel extension that satisfies the same invariants
as IRC, Nostr, and the other bundled channel plugins — but lives entirely in
`extensions/pulseboard/` with no modifications to any existing file.

**Constraint**: Only new files under `extensions/pulseboard/` may be created.
Consequence: no `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` SDK facade can be added. The `src/runtime-api.ts`
barrel must therefore re-export from individual general `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths directly
instead of a dedicated channel facade (like how `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` works for IRC).

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Plugin / channel ID | `pulseboard` | Must match dir name, package name, channel id per naming invariant |
| Package name | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | `@openclaw/<id>` — no suffix needed |
| `npmSpec` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` | Must equal package name per invariant |
| Chat types | `["direct", "group"]` | Supports user DMs and board posts |
| Text chunk limit | `4000` characters | Per spec |
| Board target prefix | `!board-name` | Analogous to IRC `#channel`; distinguishes boards from user DMs |
| DM policy default | `"pairing"` | Safe default, consistent with IRC |
| Group policy default | `"allowlist"` | Safe default, consistent with IRC |
| Gateway | Passive stub (no real network) | Fictional platform — no real SDK to call |
| Send | Stub returning timestamp-based ID | Same reason |

---

## File Structure

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # Plugin manifest
├── package.json                  # NPM package + openclaw channel metadata
├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry
├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry
├── api.ts                        # Public barrel
└── src/
    ├── runtime-api.ts            # Internal SDK re-exports (no dedicated facade)
    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── types.ts                  # Domain types
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schema + buildChannelConfigSchema
    ├── accounts.ts               # Account listing + resolution
    ├── normalize.ts              # Target normalization utilities
    ├── send.ts                   # Outbound send stub
    └── channel.ts                # pulseboardPlugin via createChatChannelPlugin
```

No test files are required for the plan scope, but `src/channel.test.ts` could be added as a
separate follow-up.

---

## File-by-File Specification

### `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest — only `id`, `channels`, and an empty `configSchema` (same as IRC/Nostr):

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Invariant**: `id` = `"pulseboard"` must match the directory name, package name anchor, and
`openclaw.channel.id` in `package.json`.

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": { "optional": true }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Boards + DMs)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Real-time bulletin boards with DM and board-post routing.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board", "bulletin-board"],
      "systemImage": "doc.richtext",
      "quickstartAllowFrom": true
    },
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    }
  }
}
```

No runtime `dependencies` block because the platform is fictional — no external SDK is needed. All
imports come from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` (resolved at runtime via `openclaw`).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`

```typescript
